<section class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-amber-50 p-5 text-sm text-amber-900">
  <h2 class="font-semibold">Safety & limitations</h2>
  <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
    <li>These are estimates. Always follow the dosing and safety directions printed on your product's label — it overrides any calculator.</li>
    <li>Never mix pool chemicals together or add water to chemicals; add chemicals to water. Store and handle in a ventilated area, away from children.</li>
    <li>Results assume balanced water (pH 7.2–7.6) and reasonably accurate volume. Very high cyanuric acid (CYA) can require more chlorine to be effective.</li>
    <li>Re-test the water before swimming and wait until free chlorine returns to 1–5 ppm.</li>
    <li>This tool does not provide professional or medical advice.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
